<item>
            <title>[LOG4J2-99] MapRewritePolicy always behaves like mode &quot;Add&quot;</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-99</link>
                <project id="12310790" key="LOG4J2">Log4j 2</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hello!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The &quot;rewrite&quot; method of org.apache.logging.log4j.core.appender.rewrite.MapRewritePolicy always calls&lt;br/&gt;
newMap.putAll(map);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;which causes the mode &quot;Update&quot; to also behave like mode &quot;Add&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Best Regards,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Das&lt;/p&gt;</description>
